Source: liblasx2lsx
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: liblasx2lsx contributors
Build-Depends: gcc (>= 8.3), binutils

Package: liblasx2lsx
Architecture: loongarch64
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.28)
Description: LASX instruction emulation library
 LASX (LoongArch SIMD Extension, 256-bit vector instruction)
 software emulation library via SIGILL trap + LD_PRELOAD.
 Runs LASX programs on platforms lacking 256-bit vector
 support (2K3000, 3B6000M, etc.).
 .
 Features:
  - Pure C emulation for all ~700 LASX instructions
  - JIT translation to LSX (128-bit) with use-def optimization
  - Loop detection and xvmap-based loop JIT
  - Multi-thread safe via pthread TLS
  - MIT licensed
